It seems okay, but that's we use quad instead of triangle. Without the wireframe, we can clearly see the artifact at the corner where we use triangle. And if the shape got pushed back a little bit more like we have a square close to the round bevel of cylinder, we would have artifact as well even though with a quad geo.Â 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

So a better solution in this case would be to support the corner bevel geo with a spread out style instead of a converge style.Â 

In order to apply the spread out style, we need to have more points(vertices) to connect to, in other words, the cylinder needs to have more subdivisions. How much more? We normally use 8-sides to deal with round shape, so a good rule of thumb is to use multiples of 8, like 16, 24, etc. Here we use 16.Â
